                <head>31. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On August 15, Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> prepared a
                    memorandum entitled “United States Post-Geneva Policy.” The memorandum was
                    approved by the President and transmitted to all United States Chiefs of Mission
                    on the same day. It was subsequently circulated among United States officials as
                    position paper POM B–7/51, August 24. For text, see volume V, page 551.</p>
            </div>
